# User Communication Standards

## Communication Strategy

- Document purpose and goals for each communication type
- Apply consistent voice and tone guidelines
- Implement communication frequency limits
- Create user journey-based communication flows
- Document user feedback mechanisms
- Measure and optimize communication effectiveness

## Message Content

- Create value-focused messaging
- Apply consistent terminology and language
- Implement proper call-to-action design
- Ensure accuracy of all content and links
- Apply personalization appropriately
- Test content for clarity and effectiveness

## Dark Mode Optimization (REQUIRED - 2024)

- Implement dark mode styles using `@media (prefers-color-scheme: dark)`
- Test dark mode rendering in Apple Mail, Gmail, Outlook
- Use semantic color variables that adapt to light and dark modes
- Ensure 4.5:1 color contrast ratio in both light and dark modes
- Apply proper logo and image handling for dark backgrounds
- Create fallback styles for email clients without dark mode support
- Test dark mode with actual devices and email clients
- Document dark mode testing results and client support
- Implement transparent PNG logos or SVGs that work in both modes
- Avoid pure white backgrounds and pure black text in dark mode

## Multi-Brand Support

- Implement brand-specific email templates and styling
- Apply appropriate sender names and addresses by brand
- Create brand-specific unsubscribe and preference centers
- Maintain consistent brand voice within each product line
- Document brand guidelines for email communications
- Apply proper brand segmentation in email marketing platform

## Delivery Optimization

- Implement send-time optimization
- Apply proper segmentation for targeting
- Create A/B testing strategy for optimization
- Document optimal sending frequency
- Implement engagement-based sending rules
- Apply user timezone awareness

